{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869020618,"sessionID":"ses_285f60e0affe0eDyuP2cc5cyQ1","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0a2592001gU031E2rGsVpQg","messageID":"msg_d7a0a0345001LpQVeX0Tv5uUer","sessionID":"ses_285f60e0affe0eDyuP2cc5cyQ1","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_1650b8bba68a429196fb5e9d","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI toolkit to enable users to invoke deployed agents and check their status. These commands complete the core CLI workflow alongside existing `pack`, `build`, and `publish` commands.\n\n## Problem Statement\n\nUsers need to:\n1. Invoke deployed agents with custom payloads and headers\n2. Check the status of deployed agents (running, not published, error states)\n3. Support both AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR) and standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment/Service)\n\nCurrently, only `pack`, `build`, and `publish` commands are available. The `invoke` and `status` commands are specified but not yet implemented.\n\n## Solution\n\n### 1. Implement `invoke` Command\n\n**Location:** `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n\n**Command Signature:**\n```python\ndef invoke(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n    header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n1. Parse `payload` as JSON, exit with code 1 if invalid\n2. Parse `header_list` into dict, validate `key:value` format\n3. Resolve workspace path to absolute Path\n4. Instantiate `InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n5. Call `runtime.invoke(workspace_path, payload, headers)`\n6. Print response using Rich console\n7. Handle errors via `_handle_error`\n\n**Header Parsing Logic:**\n```python\nheaders = {}\nif header_list:\n    for h in header_list:\n        if \":\" not in h:\n            # print error, exit(1)\n        key, value = h.split(\":\", 1)\n        headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n```\n\n**Payload Parsing:**\n```python\ntry:\n    payload_dict = json.loads(payload)\nexcept json.JSONDecodeError:\n    # print invalid JSON error, exit(1)\n```\n\n### 2. Implement `status` Command\n\n**Location:** `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n\n**Command Signature:**\n```python\ndef status(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n1. Resolve workspace path to absolute Path\n2. Instantiate `StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n3. Call `runtime.get_status(workspace_path, provider=provider)`\n4. Display results in Rich Table with columns: Property, Value\n5. Exit with code 1 if status is `not_published` or `error`\n\n**Table Columns:**\n- Agent Name\n- Status\n- Agent ID (if available)\n- Agent Endpoint (if available)\n- Provider Type\n- Namespace\n- Additional provider-specific info\n\n### 3. Error Handling\n\nUse existing `_handle_error` helper:\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Print error message and exit with code 1.\"\"\"\n    console = Console(stderr=True)\n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/]\")\n    if verbose:\n        console.print_exception()\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n**Special Error Cases:**\n- Invalid JSON payload → exit before `_handle_error`\n- Invalid header format → exit before `_handle_error`\n- Missing workspace → raised by runtime, handled by `_handle_error`\n- Not published (`status == \"not_published\"`) → print guidance, exit(1)\n\n### 4. Runtime Classes\n\n**InvokeRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`):\n- `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")`\n- `invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any`\n- `_validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]`\n- `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube(...)` - async method for CR-based invocation\n- `_direct_http_invocation(...)` - async method for direct HTTP call\n\n**StatusRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`):\n- `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")`\n- `get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n- `_get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]` - for standard K8s provider\n- `_get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]` - for AgentRuntime CR\n\n### 5. Provider-Specific Behavior\n\n**AgentCube Provider (`provider=agentcube`):**\n- Uses `AgentCubeProvider` service\n- CR API: `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`\n- Invoke URL format: `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n- Status from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when available\n\n**Kubernetes Provider (`provider=k8s`):**\n- Uses `KubernetesProvider` service\n- Standard Deployment + NodePort Service\n- Invoke via `service_url` from deployment info\n- Status from pod readiness/replicas\n\n### 6. Session Management\n\nWhen metadata contains `session_id`:\n- Add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (or `x-agentcube-session-id`) to invoke requests\n- Same spelling as SDK uses for consistency\n\n### 7. File Changes Required\n\n| File | Change Type | Description |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Modify | Add `invoke` and `status` command functions, register with Typer app |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | Create/Modify | Implement InvokeRuntime class with invoke logic |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | Create/Modify | Implement StatusRuntime class with status retrieval |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Modify | Add `StatusRuntime` to exports if needed |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Modify | Ensure runtimes are re-exported |\n\n### 8. Dependencies\n\nAlready available from existing implementation:\n- `MetadataService` - load workspace metadata\n- `AgentCubeProvider` - CR-based operations\n- `KubernetesProvider` - standard K8s operations\n- `AgentMetadata` - Pydantic model for metadata\n- Rich - for console output and tables\n- httpx/requests - for HTTP invocations\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n1. Test header parsing (valid/invalid formats)\n2. Test payload parsing (valid/invalid JSON)\n3. Test `InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites`\n4. Test `StatusRuntime.get_status` for different states\n\n### Integration Tests\n1. Mock Kubernetes API responses\n2. Mock HTTP endpoints for invocation\n3. Test full command flow with mocked runtimes\n\n### Test Files\n- `tests/cli/test_invoke_command.py`\n- `tests/cli/test_status_command.py`\n- `tests/runtime/test_invoke_runtime.py`\n- `tests/runtime/test_status_runtime.py`\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n1. **Phase 1: Core Runtime Implementation**\n   - Implement `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` method\n   - Implement `StatusRuntime.get_status()` method\n   - Add provider-specific status retrieval methods\n\n2. **Phase 2: CLI Command Implementation**\n   - Add `invoke` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n   - Add `status` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n   - Register commands with Typer app\n\n3. **Phase 3: Error Handling & Validation**\n   - Add payload JSON validation\n   - Add header format validation\n   - Implement error handling with verbose mode\n\n4. **Phase 4: Testing**\n   - Write unit tests for runtime classes\n   - Write integration tests for CLI commands\n   - Test error scenarios\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube invoke --help` shows correct options\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube status --help` shows correct options\n- [ ] Invalid JSON payload exits with code 1 and error message\n- [ ] Invalid header format exits with code 1 and error message\n- [ ] Status command displays Rich table with agent info\n- [ ] Status exits with code 1 when agent not published\n- [ ] Invoke command sends correct headers including session ID\n- [ ] Provider flag switches between `agentcube` and `k8s` behavior\n- [ ] Verbose mode shows traceback on errors\n- [ ] All existing tests continue to pass\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| Kubernetes client not initialized | High | Clear error messages, check prerequisites |\n| Missing router_url/workload_manager_url | Medium | Validate in metadata loading, provide setup guidance |\n| Async invocation complexity | Medium | Use asyncio.run() wrapper for sync CLI context |\n| Session ID header naming inconsistency | Low | Follow SDK convention (`x-agentcube-session-id`) |\n\n## References\n\n- `cli-toolkit/design.md` - CLI package layout and command signatures\n- `cli-toolkit/spec.md` - Detailed requirements and scenarios\n- `python-sdk/design.md` - SDK client patterns for invocation\n- `deployment/client-go.md` - CR API group/version/plural details\n"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775869020607,"end":1775869020615}}}}
