{"type":"text","timestamp":1775869035195,"sessionID":"ses_285f60e0affe0eDyuP2cc5cyQ1","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0b013c001Z9Uk1Krcpl7jvy","messageID":"msg_d7a0af91e001qER67S69xAilnx","sessionID":"ses_285f60e0affe0eDyuP2cc5cyQ1","type":"text","text":"Now I'll write the proposal for AR-023 in the appropriate location:","time":{"start":1775869035192,"end":1775869035192}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869082407,"sessionID":"ses_285f60e0affe0eDyuP2cc5cyQ1","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0b02ba001qJUjTwiZ83Pi5K","messageID":"msg_d7a0af91e001qER67S69xAilnx","sessionID":"ses_285f60e0affe0eDyuP2cc5cyQ1","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_41ef1875d64449eebe4317ea","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI toolkit to enable users to invoke deployed agents and check their status. These commands complete the core CLI workflow alongside existing `pack`, `build`, and `publish` commands.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:\n- `invoke` command - POST JSON payloads to deployed agent endpoints\n- `status` command - Display agent deployment status in Rich table format\n- Support for two providers: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment/Service)\n- Header parsing and validation\n- Payload JSON parsing and validation\n- Session ID management\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Global Options\n\nBoth commands inherit global options from the Typer app:\n- `--workspace` / `-f` - Workspace directory path (default: `\".\"`)\n- `--provider` - Target provider: `\"agentcube\"` or `\"k8s\"` (default: `\"agentcube\"`)\n- `--verbose` - Enable detailed logging (default: `False`)\n\n### invoke Command\n\n**Signature:**\n```python\ndef invoke(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\"),\n    payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\"),\n    header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n1. Parse `payload` as JSON, exit with code 1 if invalid\n2. Parse `header_list` into dict, validate `key:value` format\n3. Load workspace metadata to get agent endpoint\n4. Instantiate `InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n5. Call `runtime.invoke(workspace_path, payload_dict, headers)`\n6. Print response using Rich console\n7. Handle errors via `_handle_error`\n\n**Header Format:**\n- Multiple `--header` flags allowed: `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"`\n- Must contain exactly one `:` separator\n- Format: `key:value` (whitespace trimmed)\n\n**Session Management:**\n- If metadata contains `session_id`, add header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- User-provided headers take precedence\n\n### status Command\n\n**Signature:**\n```python\ndef status(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n1. Load workspace metadata\n2. Instantiate `StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n3. Call `runtime.get_status(workspace_path, provider=provider)`\n4. Display results in Rich Table\n5. Exit with code 1 if status is `not_published` or `error`\n\n**Table Columns:**\n| Column | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| Property | Status property name |\n| Value | Property value |\n\n**Rows to Display:**\n- Agent Name\n- Status (published, not_published, error, running, etc.)\n- Agent ID (if available)\n- Agent Endpoint (if available)\n- Provider Type\n- Namespace\n- Additional provider-specific info\n\n### Error Handling\n\n**Standard Errors:**\n| Error | Exit Code | Message |\n|-------|-----------|---------|\n| Invalid JSON payload | 1 | \"Invalid payload JSON: {error}\" |\n| Invalid header format | 1 | \"Invalid header format. Expected 'key:value'\" |\n| Workspace not found | 1 | \"Workspace directory does not exist\" |\n| Not published | 1 | \"Agent not published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first\" |\n| Runtime error | 1 | \"Error {command}: {error}\" (with traceback if verbose) |\n\n**Helper Function:**\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Print error message and exit with code 1.\"\"\"\n    console = Console(stderr=True)\n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/]\")\n    if verbose:\n        console.print_exception()\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### invoke Runtime Implementation\n\n**File:** `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n\n**Class Structure:**\n```python\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\"):\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.provider = provider\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n    \n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Any:\n        # Load metadata\n        # Validate prerequisites (agent_id, endpoint)\n        # Route to provider-specific invocation\n        # Return response\n```\n\n**Provider-Specific Invocation:**\n\n**AgentCube Provider (AgentRuntime CR):**\n- Use `AgentCubeProvider` to get CR object\n- Construct URL: `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n- POST payload with `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- Handle async HTTP request\n\n**Kubernetes Provider (Deployment/Service):**\n- Use `KubernetesProvider` to get deployment info\n- Get `service_url` from metadata (`http://localhost:{node_port}`)\n- POST payload directly to service URL\n\n### status Runtime Implementation\n\n**File:** `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n\n**Class Structure:**\n```python\nclass StatusRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\"):\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.provider = provider\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n    \n    def get_status(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        provider: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        # Load metadata\n        # Check if published (agent_id exists)\n        # Route to provider-specific status check\n        # Return status dict\n```\n\n**Status Values:**\n| Status | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `not_published` | No `agent_id` in metadata |\n| `running` | Deployment ready, pods healthy |\n| `error` | Deployment exists but not ready |\n| `unknown` | Cannot determine status |\n\n**AgentCube Provider Status:**\n- Query CR via `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime(name, namespace)`\n- Extract status from `cr_object[\"status\"]`\n- Fields: `status`, `agentEndpoint`, `phase`, `conditions`\n\n**Kubernetes Provider Status:**\n- Query Deployment via `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status(agent_name)`\n- Check replica availability and pod readiness\n- Fields: `replicas`, `ready_replicas`, `available_replicas`\n\n### Provider Selection\n\nBoth commands use the `--provider` flag to determine behavior:\n\n```python\nif provider == \"agentcube\":\n    runtime = StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=\"agentcube\")\n    # Uses AgentCubeProvider internally\nelif provider == \"k8s\":\n    runtime = StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=\"k8s\")\n    # Uses KubernetesProvider internally\nelse:\n    raise ValueError(f\"Unknown provider: {provider}\")\n```\n\n## File Changes\n\n### Files to Create\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | InvokeRuntime class |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | StatusRuntime class |\n\n### Files to Modify\n\n| File | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Add `invoke` and `status` commands, register with Typer app |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Export new runtime classes |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Optionally export `StatusRuntime` |\n\n### Dependencies\n\nAlready available from existing implementation:\n- `MetadataService` - load workspace metadata\n- `AgentCubeProvider` - CR-based operations  \n- `KubernetesProvider` - standard K8s operations\n- `AgentMetadata` - Pydantic model\n- `rich` - console output and tables\n- `httpx` or `requests` - HTTP invocations\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**test_invoke_command.py:**\n- Test header parsing (valid/invalid formats)\n- Test payload parsing (valid/invalid JSON)\n- Test command registration with Typer\n\n**test_status_command.py:**\n- Test status table rendering\n- Test exit codes for different statuses\n\n**test_invoke_runtime.py:**\n- Test `_validate_invoke_prerequisites`\n- Test provider selection logic\n- Test session ID header injection\n\n**test_status_runtime.py:**\n- Test `_get_cr_k8s_status` with mock CR\n- Test `_get_k8s_status` with mock deployment\n- Test status determination logic\n\n### Integration Tests\n\nMock external services:\n- Mock Kubernetes API responses\n- Mock HTTP endpoints for invocation\n- Test full command flow with mocked runtimes\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube invoke --help` shows correct options and descriptions\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube status --help` shows correct options and descriptions\n- [ ] Invalid JSON payload exits with code 1 and red error message\n- [ ] Invalid header format exits with code 1 with guidance\n- [ ] Status command displays Rich table with agent info\n- [ ] Status exits with code 1 when `agent_id` is missing\n- [ ] Invoke command sends `x-agentcube-session-id` when metadata has `session_id`\n- [ ] Provider flag switches between `agentcube` and `k8s` behavior\n- [ ] Verbose mode shows full traceback on errors\n- [ ] All existing CLI tests continue to pass\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` with InvokeRuntime class\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` with StatusRuntime class\n- [ ] Add `invoke` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n- [ ] Add `status` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n- [ ] Register commands with Typer app\n- [ ] Implement header parsing and validation\n- [ ] Implement payload JSON parsing\n- [ ] Implement error handling with verbose mode\n- [ ] Update `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` exports\n- [ ] Write unit tests for runtime classes\n- [ ] Write integration tests for CLI commands\n- [ ] Verify against spec scenarios\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| Kubernetes client not initialized | High | Clear error messages, check prerequisites in runtime |\n| Missing router_url/workload_manager_url | Medium | Validate in metadata loading, provide setup guidance |\n| Async invocation in sync CLI | Medium | Use `asyncio.run()` wrapper for async HTTP calls |\n| Session header naming inconsistency | Low | Follow SDK convention (`x-agentcube-session-id`) |\n\n## References\n\n- `cli-toolkit/design.md` - CLI package layout and command signatures\n- `cli-toolkit/spec.md` - Detailed requirements and scenarios for invoke/status\n- `python-sdk/design.md` - SDK client patterns for invocation\n- `deployment/client-go.md` - CR API group/version/plural details\n- AR-022 proposal - Previous CLI command implementation pattern\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-023/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-023/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-023/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775869082393,"end":1775869082404}}}}
